

# 🎨 Full UI Description — Readly Platform

---

## 🌍 1. Public Landing Page (Before Login)

### 🎯 Goal

Explain the concept quickly to parents/educators and attract children.

### Layout

* **Top Navigation Bar**

  * Logo (left)
  * Links: *How it works*, *For Parents*, *Stories*, *Login*
  * Primary CTA button: **Start Playing**

* **Hero Section**

  * Large illustration (storybook + puzzle vibe)
  * Headline: playful, rounded font
  * Subtext: short educational value statement
  * Buttons:

    * Start as Guest
    * Parent / Educator Login

* **How It Works (3 steps)**

  * Read a story
  * Solve a riddle
  * Learn & level up

* **Trust Section**

  * Icons: Safe for kids, Educational, Adaptive
  * No ads / privacy friendly

* **Footer**

  * Legal links
  * Language switch
  * Contact

---

## 🔐 2. Authentication UI

### Login / Register Modal or Page

* Tabs:

  * Child
  * Parent / Educator
  * Admin (hidden or protected)

#### Fields

* Email (for parent/admin)
* Nickname (for child)
* Password
* Optional: avatar selection (child)

#### UX Notes

* Friendly copy for kids
* Clear separation of roles
* Error messages are soft and encouraging

---

## 🧒 3. Child Home Dashboard

### 🎯 Goal

Make the child feel safe, motivated, and curious.

### Layout

* **Top Bar**

  * Avatar (left)
  * Progress bar (stars / levels)
  * Sound toggle (TTS on/off)

* **Main Area**

  * “Continue Your Story” card (highlighted)
  * Story map (horizontal or vertical path)

    * Locked stories (blurred)
    * Current story (animated)
    * Completed stories (checkmark/star)

* **Bottom Navigation (mobile-first)**

  * Home
  * Stories
  * Rewards
  * Profile

---

## 📖 4. Story Reading Screen

### Layout

* **Header**

  * Story title
  * Progress indicator (e.g. page dots)

* **Story Content**

  * Large readable text
  * Line spacing optimized for kids
  * Highlighted keywords (optional)

* **Audio Controls**

  * Play / Pause narration
  * Speed control (slow / normal)

* **Next Button**

  * Appears after minimum reading time

### UX Notes

* No distractions
* Gentle page transitions
* Background color adapts to story mood

---

## 🧩 5. Riddle Screen (Core Experience)

### Layout

* **Riddle Card (centered)**

  * Short riddle text
  * Illustration (if available)

* **Answer Area**

  * Input field (large, friendly)
  * OR multiple-choice cards

* **Actions**

  * Submit answer
  * Hint button (glows after wrong attempt)

---

### Answer Feedback States

#### ✅ Correct Answer

* Animation (stars/confetti)
* Positive message
* “Continue story” button

#### 🟡 Almost Correct

* Encouraging message
* Subtle hint offered

#### ❌ Incorrect

* Gentle feedback
* Hint becomes active

---

## 💡 6. Hint UI (AI-powered)

### Hint Panel (Slide-up / Modal)

* Title: “Let’s think together”
* Hint level indicator (1 / 2 / 3)
* Hint content:

  * Text
  * Image
  * Audio (optional)

### UX Rules

* Never shows full answer
* Tone adapts to child performance
* Cooldown between hints

